The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Rabindranath Mahanta, 23, a resident of Dum Dum, drowned in the sea in Puri on Saturday morning. Police said Mahanta, who went to Puri on a 10-day tour with his parents, did not know swimming and was swept away by waves. He was washed ashore unconscious some time later and died while being taken to hospital. 

 Two persons were critically injured after the Tata Sumo they were travelling in was hit by a Matador near Chetla bridge on Sunday morning. Police said the Matador had lost control. 

 More than a hundred residents of Liluah blocked National Highway 6 on Sunday morning, protesting the bad condition of roads and inadequate lighting in their locality. Police said the blockade lasted more than two hours, from 9 am. Traffic on the highway was disrupted for an even longer period.

 The body of a 30-year-old unidentified man was found in Kestopur canal, on the northern fringes of the city, on Sunday evening. Police said the body bore stab injuries. A preliminary probe suggests the man was murdered elsewhere. The body has been sent for post-mortem. 

 A case was registered on Sunday against the absconding owner of a lubricant-manufacturing unit in Mahestala, on the city?s southern fringes, where a fire broke out on Saturday. A forensic team will visit the site on Monday. 

 A fire broke out in a godown on the ground floor of a highrise at the Ripon Street-AJC Bose Road crossing at 7.15 pm on Sunday. Two fire tenders brought the blaze under control. A preliminary probe suggests the fire was caused by an electrical short-circuit.

 A fire broke out on the first floor of a residential building in Phoolbagan late on Saturday. Two tenders from Maniktala station rushed to the site and doused the blaze in an hour. 

 An armed gang of six robbed goods worth Rs 2 lakh from the premises of an electrical transformer-manufacturing unit in Malipanchghora, Howrah, early on Sunday. Police said the robbers overpowered the lone guard and took away transformer parts in a truck. No one has been arrested.

